	(257,NULL,40,2,'Mimic','mimic','Poetic and prescient, this virtuosic solo performance from Raymond Scannell (Infinite Lives)','<p><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16.799999237060547px;\">Poetic and prescient, this virtuosic solo performance from Raymond Scannell (Infinite Lives), tells the story of Julian Neary, whose childhood gift for mimicry &ndash; from Columbo and Jimmy Stewart to Billie Holiday and Morrissey &ndash; becomes his ticket out of 1980s Ireland, until the chaos he sees in the outside world reflects his own chaos within.&nbsp;</span><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: #990033; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #666666; text-decoration: none; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\" href=\"http://www.tobaccofactorytheatres.com/shows/detail/mimic\">more info...</a></p>','','Bs31jp','51.4422212','-2.614305599999966',NULL,NULL,1,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,'2014-07-01 00:00:01','2014-07-01 00:00:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0),
	(259,NULL,39,2,'Stalin\'s daughter','stalins_daughter','The incredible true story of how Josef Stalinâ€™s daughter came to make her new life in Clifton, Bristol.','<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">The incredible true story of how Josef Stalin&rsquo;s daughter came to make her new life in Clifton, Bristol.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\"><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">They never ask me who I am, or why I came. Only when I plan on leaving.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">Leaving three husbands and the fall of the Soviet Union in her wake, Svetlana Alliluyeva seeks a place to reflect on the horrors of her past and to escape her father&rsquo;s name.</p>\r\n<p 